@davidhalter Resolves #554, Jedi now understands `enumerate`.

I took a similar approach to `reversed` and a few other stdlib functions.  Let me know what you think.  Just started poking around the jedi codebase this weekend, thought this was a good place to start contributing.

Thanks so much for building this awesome library!

These modifications allow a user to create custom regions in Python. They just need to add the module to the network and then they can create their custom region. Additionally, I updated network_api_demo to show how to use a custom region.

Fixes #2057

